I thought it would be fun to tell you a little more of the story behind 
“Keep Looking Up.” 

I wrote this song in 2015 with @garciaofficial . We thought it was a great song, but we were only choosing 12 songs for the record, and this one did not make the list. We turned it in to the label as a demo, but the timing wasn’t right. 

I have over 100 songs like this that have never been heard. I do believe that one day people will hear them, whether it’s me singing them or someone else. 

When I was 19 @kvministries prophesied over me at a church in Franklin TN that my voice would be a trumpet to my generation. Then a few years ago I was in another gathering with @kvministries and He encouraged artist and worship leaders to go back and listen to some of their old songs. I did that and was stirred to put out “I”ll fight for you”and “Keep Looking Up.” 

Thank you @kvministries for being a prophet and leader to us!!! When a prophet speaks it is important to listen. 

After being stirred to put these 2 song out I started working on them and was blessed to have @lael produce both songs and @iamjoe_l  join me on “Keep Looking Up.” 

I want to encourage other artist and worship leaders reading this to go and listen to the songs God has given you and ask Him, if maybe someone needs to hear it? 

I don’t release songs for it to have success, I do it out of obedience because God knows if someone needs these words :) 

Love u guys so much and just felt to share more of this. 

I am not one for long captions or all the details. But I wrote this out of obedience. ✊🏼

God knows all and His timing is right! 

Don’t bury something that God meant for you to multiply. 

-BN

Was unloading groceries. Thought of a girl I know, and felt like God gave me this song for her. Just wrote it on the spot and posted right away.I felt like someone needed to hear it. Some of the lyrics will prob change. Songs come from heaven. They are a lot like prayers. 🙏🏼

Wrote this song and a couple days later @godframe posted this reel’ Loved it so much I had to put it right here!! Should we drop this?? 🤩

I love what he wrote ⬇️

“I haven’t released any of my own songs in about two years. If I’m being honest, really thinking my time as a vocalist was over. But if I am really being real, I was actually struggling with doubt and insecurity. When I saw this clip of Britt and read the story behind it, I fell in love with the lyrics and message. She put it out there, raw and uncut, still under construction, and straight from her heart. Definitely reminded me that I’ve got more hope to give through Music. “ 

Keep dreaming Friends ☁️ ….This is why I make music, to encourage others that they can dream and overcome anything in this life! 

I hope you know how loved you are. 💙

Setting up tonight for our very first @anchorhousecreatives event that happens this Friday!! It is a private event but soon you will be able to sign up to be a part of this creative community!! 🙌🏼 Can’t wait to tell you more, but just one step at a time!! ⚓️🏠🌱

Dream Big.

Last September we gathered with some of our friends and family and spontaneously wrote this song called “We Say Yes.” ( We are finishing it now 💛 ) 

I remember waking up the morning of the gathering with such anticipation and joy. The thing I was most excited about was space. Space for people and space for presence. I will share more on this later. It did not make sense for us to gather on this specific night. We had to drive to a different city 3 hours down the road after, but we felt a pull and we said yes. When this night started it was very evident that this simple, yet profound night was a seed. A seed into something more that we knew would come with time. After this night in Franklin TN, we made our way to Indiana for a powerful night with 100 women squished into one living room, ha. Then down to San Antonio, Texas where we met at another boutique and watched people from all walks of life walk through the doors and encounter a love they had never known. It has honestly been one of my favorite things I’ve ever been a part of. 

All this to say we are doing more “We Say Yes” nights this year and I am stirred for it. These nights are about community. We have local coffee, local boutiques, and we watch people’s hearts open up. It’s just so fun!! We would love to partner with you and come to your city. If you are interested in that, DM us and we will get that conversation started. We already have 5 cities we are planning and we will share those soon! 

Stay tuned for this song “ We Say Yes” 
and be watching to see if we are doing a 
“We Say Yes” night in your city!!
